Ramez to Join Commercial International Bank as Vice Chairman

-- B y   M a h m o u d   K a s s e m
-- 
2011-12-01T07:50:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/ramez-to-join-commercial-international-bank-as-vice-chairman-1-.html
Hisham Ramez, a former Egyptian
central bank deputy governor, will join  Commercial International
Bank SAE (COMI)  as vice chairman and managing director, the bank said.  Ramez will head the institutional and consumer businesses
at  Egypt â€™s biggest publicly traded bank and Hisham Ezz Al-Arab,
chairman and managing director, will oversee the regulatory
departments with special focus on strategic issues, Cairo-based
Commercial International said in a Regulatory News Service
statement today.  Ramez will start at Commercial International as soon as the
appointment is cleared by the Central Bank of Egypt, the bank
said.  Shares of Commercial International Bank gained 0.8 percent
to 23.25 Egyptian pounds at the close in Cairo yesterday,
valuing the bank at 13.7 billion pounds ($2.28 billion).  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
